## Migration Analysis

Your code has three patterns that break on .NET 8:

| API | Problem on .NET 8 |
|-----|-------------------|
| `Thread.Abort()` | Throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` (SYSLIB0006) |
| `Thread.Interrupt()` | Obsolete (SYSLIB0046 in .NET 9), unreliable wake mechanism |
| `ManualResetEvent` + manual lock | Race condition — multiple enqueues can be lost with single `Reset()` |

**Patterns identified:**
1. **Cancellable work loop** — `RunLoop()` infinite loop
2. **Blocking call interruption** — `WaitOne()` needs cancellation-aware wake
3. **Timeout enforcement** — `Abort()` as hard-kill fallback

---

## Migrated Code (.NET 8)

```csharp
using System.Threading.Channels;

public class EventProcessor : IAsyncDisposable
{
    private readonly Channel<string> _channel = Channel.CreateUnbounded<string>();
    private readonly CancellationTokenSource _cts = new();
    private Task? _processingTask;

    public void Start()
    {
        _processingTask = Task.Run(() => RunLoopAsync(_cts.Token));
    }

    private async Task RunLoopAsync(CancellationToken token)
    {
        try
        {
            await foreach (var item in _channel.Reader.ReadAllAsync(token))
            {
                Handle(item);
            }
        }
        catch (OperationCanceledException) when (token.IsCancellationRequested)
        {
            // Graceful shutdown — expected
        }
    }

    public void Enqueue(string item)
    {
        if (!_channel.Writer.TryWrite(item))
            throw new InvalidOperationException("Channel closed.");
    }

    public async ValueTask StopAsync(TimeSpan? timeout = null)
    {
        _channel.Writer.Complete();           // Signal no more items
        _cts.CancelAfter(timeout ?? TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5)); // Hard deadline

        if (_processingTask is not null)
            await _processingTask.ConfigureAwait(false);
    }

    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync()
    {
        await StopAsync().ConfigureAwait(false);
        _cts.Dispose();
    }

    private void Handle(string item) { /* your logic */ }
}
```

